<item>
            <title>[SOLR-194] SimplePostTool uses hardcoded UTF-8 encoding to read files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-194</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  java -Dfile.encoding=iso-8859-1 -jar post.jar &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8983/solr/update&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8983/solr/update&lt;/a&gt; utf8-example.xml&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;posts incorrect data, apparently utf8-example.xml is read using the JVM&apos;s encoding.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As a workaround before we fix this, use&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  java -Dfile.encoding=UTF-8 -jar post.jar &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8983/solr/update&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8983/solr/update&lt;/a&gt; utf8-example.xml&lt;/p&gt;</description>
