                            <comment id="12482690" author="bdelacretaz" created="Wed, 21 Mar 2007 09:38:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The above problem is fixed in revision 520817 by hardcoding the UTF-8 encoding to read files.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ll need to use a the XML parser to read these files cleanly, especially once &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-190&quot; title=&quot;Encoding declaration of POSTed XML documents is ignored&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-190&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-190&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12482691" author="bdelacretaz" created="Wed, 21 Mar 2007 09:39:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Both issues will need to be fixed in order to post non UTF-8 documents using the SimplePostTool&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
